<P>It will no doubt be objected, that I did not &s;ettle the partner&s;hip accounts on t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> demi&s;e of William Alli&s;on&mdash;that I did not apply the certificates to the payment <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> partner&s;hip debts&mdash;and that I did not accept the offer of Doctor M'Henry&mdash;th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> of taking the goods at the apprai&s;ement and his engagement to pay Francis All<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">+&s;on. To the two fir&s;t I have already replied in this narrative&mdash;to the la&s;t I an&s;w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> that &pound;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">00 was all that was offered for what &s;tood us in &pound;2700, that at the ti<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> I had a hope to rai&s;e more money in ca&s;h for them&mdash;that &s;ome had already be<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> &s;ent to vendue&mdash;and that the &s;ums to be paid to Levi Holling&s;worth I was co<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">+&s;tantly dunned for&mdash;and had I not made payments from time to time as I did. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;uit would have been in&s;tituted and the property of the heirs as well in lands, &amp;c&punc; as the certificates would have been &s;acrificed&mdash;and I thought le&s;s lo&s;s would <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> occa&s;ioned by &s;ale of the goods&mdash;though this has proved greatly to my di&s;advantag<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"></P>
