<P>Now as William Alli&s;on by an account delivered by him to John Bleakley on the 28th of May 1787, (only fourteen days before his death) did owe a balance of &pound;2518 7 2 to Bleakley: it follows, that he had le&s;s &s;tock in the partner&s;hip by
<PB N="24" REF="046494_0024_1021786A859E52F0">
upwards of &pound;300 than this debt&mdash;and therefore he had no money of his <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;tock in the company&mdash;for credit is given to William Alli&s;on for every fart<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> which the company received of Bleakley's money, which will appear by in&s;pe<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">+on of the &s;aid account which &s;hews the balance of &pound;2518 7 2. To le&s;&s;en his <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> to the e&s;tate of David Caldwell, I was very willing to &s;ell the goods to M'Hen<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> and happy for the company it would have been could that hou&s;e have found <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> for more of them&mdash;but money could not be rai&s;ed with the&s;e&mdash;for very lit<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> ever remitted from M'Henry, but as William Alli&s;on was indebted to C<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> e&s;tate&mdash;tho&s;e goods an&s;wered him as well as ca&s;h. Could they have been <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> here for money&mdash;it would be mo&s;t certainly my advantage to have paid off <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> to Francis Alli&s;on&mdash;but this could not be done in any other way than at public <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word">.</P>
<P>That the e&s;tate of William Alli&s;on will be liable for the debts of the company a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> well as that to Bleakley will follow&mdash;becau&s;e I am in capacitated to pay any p<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> &s;ave what my lands may bring at public &s;ale&mdash;the proceeds of which mu&s;t <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">+vided in proportion among my per&s;onal creditors, as well as to the heirs aft<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> have paid off the debts of the partner&s;hip&mdash;which they can have no clai<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">+fore. Contra&s;t this with my offer of mortgaging the lands in a way &s;afe <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> heirs and not (as I thought) un&s;afe or di&s;honourable to me&mdash;becau&s;e, &s;hou<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> been helped by the intere&s;t of their friends to &s;uch office as I am able to fi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> one I mean as would require con&s;tant application&mdash;not a &s;inecure (which I hav<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> rea&s;on to expect) it would give me plea&s;ure to &s;ave from injury the heirs of a <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> who has injured me, though I believe without the lea&s;t de&s;ign.</P>
<P>To &s;hew the impracticability of &s;tating preci&s;ely the ju&s;t &s;um which the heirs <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> William Alli&s;on will have again&s;t me, it is only nece&s;&s;ary to ob&s;erve, that all deb<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> due by the company mu&s;t fir&s;t be paid, that the partner&s;hip lands mu&s;t be &s;old&mdash; that tho&s;e of Sidman cannot be even known until deci&s;ion of an amicable actio<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> in&s;tituted or agreed to be in&s;tituted in the Supreme Court, between the a&s;&s;igne<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> under the fir&s;t a&s;&s;ignment and tho&s;e under the &s;econd&mdash;for the pleading to w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> &s;everal lawyers are retained. That a que&s;tion of law may ari&s;e relative to the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">+nies received by me &s;ince the death of William Alli&s;on, for the creditors of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> Wallace and I&s;aac Sidman, as to how far the heirs are concerned in tho&s;e <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">+ions&mdash;and perhaps there may be others not now recollected by.</P>
